definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: They were carrying four or five at a time.
sentences.chinese: 他们一次要运出来四五具尸体。

sentences.english: This was the holy ikon that had been brought away from Smolensk, and had accompanied the army ever since.
sentences.chinese: 这是从斯摩棱斯克运出并且从此就跟着军队的圣像。

sentences.english: Whatever sent the precious metals out of a country impoverished it.
sentences.chinese: 而将贵金属从一个国家运出则会使其变穷。

sentences.english: Logs must be hauled out of the forest.
And the U. S. and Britain are airlifting by helicopter scores of people with special needs.
sentences.chinese: 美国和英国动用直升机把有特殊需要的人运出黎巴嫩。

sentences.english: They will case the bottles and ship them out.
sentences.chinese: 他们将把瓶子装箱然后运出去。

sentences.english: Please complete a Limited Release tag and we will ship the box.
sentences.chinese: 请填写一下免除责任行李牌，我们将运出。

sentences.english: All coal was moved from the work face by electrically-driven conveyors.
sentences.chinese: 所有的煤都用电动传送带从工作面运出来。

sentences.english: The loosened coal falls onto a conveyor for removal from the mine.
sentences.chinese: 松脱的煤块落到传送带上，被运出矿井外。

sentences.english: S . and Britain are airlifting by helicopter scores of people with special needs .
sentences.chinese: 美国和英国动用直升机把有特殊需要的人运出黎巴嫩。

sentences.english: Quote both ways. I would like to see if it is feasible to ship packaged insoles out of Asia.
sentences.chinese: 散装报价我想看看把包装的鞋垫运出亚洲是否可行。

sentences.english: The machines ordered on the 10th April were despatched to your address yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 对于4月10日所订机器，我们于昨天运出，请查收。

sentences.english: I can ship you out in my crate.
sentences.chinese: 我可以把你放在板条箱里运出去。

sentences.english: This transaction is simple and risk free and the box can be shipped out in 48hrs.
sentences.chinese: 这项交易是简单，无风险的箱运出，可在48小时。

sentences.english: “There were lorries coming out of the park with hundreds of tusks, ” she said.
sentences.chinese: 竟会有数百的象牙通过卡车运出国家公园。

sentences.english: Once removed from the mine, coal becomes merchandise available for sale.
sentences.chinese: 一旦运出了矿场，煤就成为可供销售的商品。

definition: to forward goods/to ship/to distribute/transshipment/a lucky break/change of fortune (for the better)
to break or cut in two/to sever/to cut off/(fig.) to cut off (a conversation, a flow etc)/to interrupt/(math.) to truncate
